S|# 29 · Projects (System)|> A page for the portfolio of projects/workspaces. Appears as a `project…-page.md` entry in the creator's own Briefings folder (screenshot 181510; filename truncated in the capture).
S|Purpose|A cross-workspace view of the owner's projects — the businesses each workspace represents (Vibe with AI, Canela, Valhalla, By Design) plus any client/build projects. Gives the owner the single-pane "overview of all the projects" the walkthrough repeatedly emphasizes, while partners are scoped to just their own workspace.
S|What it covers (inferred)|- A list/grid of projects with status, owning workspace, and key metrics. // - Likely overlaps with the **Software pl** portfolio view (which already lists Idea-Feed MVP, By Design, Canela Shop, Mission Control, Valhalla Tools) but framed at the *business/project* level rather than the *codebase* level. // - Entry points to each project's dedicated mission control (each project "needs their own design pages customized").
S|Relationship to other screens|- Ties to **Workspaces & Design System** (`26`) — the multi-tenant model — and the **Software pl** portfolio (`22`). // > **Confidence: Inferred.** Named in the creator's Briefings folder; no dedicated UI screenshot. The filename was partially cut off in the capture, so even the exact page name is approximate. Treat as design intent.